WEBVTT

00:03.786 --> 00:06.006
[neon sign buzzing]

00:06.136 --> 00:08.443
[Radio host]
That was "The Sacrifice,"
the Viking metal anthem

00:08.530 --> 00:11.663
that will live for the ages,
by Blood Death,

00:11.794 --> 00:13.883
as we mourn the loss of
four of its members

00:14.014 --> 00:17.060
found dead in a hotel room
in Bridgeport, Connecticut.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.324
[Cordelia]
Some whack-job berserker
named Johan

00:20.455 --> 00:22.587
blew up the biker bar
while your dad was inside.

00:22.761 --> 00:24.633
♪

00:24.720 --> 00:26.069
Who are you?

00:26.200 --> 00:28.115
I know you as you know me.

00:28.245 --> 00:30.943
"I" is "we."

00:31.074 --> 00:33.772
You have had this
power all along.

00:33.903 --> 00:35.731
You can reclaim it now.

00:35.861 --> 00:37.776
With the power of the "we."

00:38.690 --> 00:40.170
[Trending]
SHARD is about building
a church of the mind

00:40.301 --> 00:42.738
for 8 billion
worshippers.

00:43.086 --> 00:44.827
[glitching]

00:46.524 --> 00:49.005
Could you warn me
before you do that?

00:49.136 --> 00:50.659
Uh, Laura.

00:50.789 --> 00:52.139
Hi, kids.

00:52.269 --> 00:53.531
Laura.

00:53.966 --> 00:56.143
I hear we have
a common enemy.

00:57.100 --> 01:00.060
[Chad]
Alison McGovern didn't show up
to school or work yesterday.

01:00.190 --> 01:01.931
No one's seen or heard
from her since.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.107
Yo, yo, my G.
How you livin', bro?

01:04.238 --> 01:05.456
[Shadow]
What's the deal with this?

01:05.587 --> 01:06.544
[Mabel]
Three more break-ins

01:06.675 --> 01:08.155
since Alison went missing.

01:08.894 --> 01:12.811
Some sicko is stealing
ladies' unmentionables...

01:13.682 --> 01:15.379
You hurt my sister,
I'll know.

01:15.466 --> 01:17.120
She's been
through hell already.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.340
[Mr. Wednesday] So, you... you'll leave with me

01:19.427 --> 01:20.906
when the release papers come?

01:21.342 --> 01:22.647
[Demeter]
Tomorrow...

01:22.778 --> 01:25.128
Tomorrow is soon enough.

01:25.694 --> 01:26.651
[Mr. Wednesday]
Until tomorrow, then.

01:27.391 --> 01:28.566
No.

01:28.958 --> 01:30.916
No, Demeter, don't go.

01:39.664 --> 01:40.970
♪

01:44.321 --> 01:45.801
♪

01:54.157 --> 01:57.073
♪ It's been a long time ♪

01:57.160 --> 02:00.555
♪ Since I've held you
in my arms... ♪

02:03.514 --> 02:05.429
♪

02:05.603 --> 02:08.780
♪ Since I've felt,
felt your magic charm ♪

02:08.911 --> 02:11.043
I'm sorry things didn't
work out with your ex.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.481
♪ Oh you did me wrong ♪

02:13.611 --> 02:15.265
If you want to
talk about it...

02:15.439 --> 02:18.399
♪ Now you say
you want to come back ♪

02:21.706 --> 02:23.534
Well, I guess
I'll just keep driving

02:23.621 --> 02:24.753
to an unknown destination

02:24.883 --> 02:26.711
until I run out of road...

02:28.148 --> 02:30.062
♪ When I say that I... ♪

02:30.193 --> 02:32.543
Or you regain
the power of speech.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.590
Any idea when
that might be?

02:39.768 --> 02:40.943
[gasping]

02:41.073 --> 02:42.553
[tires screeching]

02:43.511 --> 02:45.034
[body thudding]

02:48.168 --> 02:49.386
What the fuck?

02:54.870 --> 02:55.784
[car door closing]

03:00.397 --> 03:03.357
[sizzling]

03:10.712 --> 03:12.540
[heavy breathing]

03:12.627 --> 03:14.150
♪

03:15.064 --> 03:16.326
Oh, shit!

03:18.241 --> 03:20.765
Where the hell did
he come from? Hey!

03:20.896 --> 03:21.984
Talk to me!

03:22.289 --> 03:24.204
A flaming body

03:24.291 --> 03:25.683
just fell out of the sky!

03:25.814 --> 03:27.859
-Be quiet.
-What? Aw, shit!

03:27.990 --> 03:29.034
Just get in the car.

03:29.165 --> 03:31.298
What? Look, I am down
for a lot of shit

03:31.428 --> 03:33.909
-but I did not sign up for
whatever the fuck that is.
-Enough. Just get in the car.

03:37.521 --> 03:39.697
♪

03:55.539 --> 03:56.453
[sighing]

03:58.238 --> 03:59.413
[tires screeching]

04:02.894 --> 04:04.505
[heavy footsteps approaching]

04:10.772 --> 04:13.209
[heavy breathing]

04:17.169 --> 04:18.910
[fire sizzling]

04:20.260 --> 04:21.739
[animalistic growling]

04:21.826 --> 04:25.177
[fire crackling]

04:25.352 --> 04:26.701
♪

04:36.319 --> 04:37.625
[growling]

04:38.800 --> 04:40.889
[choking]

04:43.195 --> 04:45.894
[truck horn blaring]

04:52.204 --> 04:53.989
♪

04:56.426 --> 04:58.515
♪

06:18.639 --> 06:21.250
♪

06:32.043 --> 06:32.914
[bell dinging]

06:33.001 --> 06:35.003
♪

06:54.805 --> 06:55.893
Can I top that up
for you, hon?

06:56.024 --> 06:57.765
Oh, just a splash.

06:57.852 --> 06:59.419
Don't let
Dr. Fallon see.

06:59.549 --> 07:00.855
He's been
all over me lately

07:00.985 --> 07:02.378
about cutting
back on caffeine.

07:03.640 --> 07:05.076
I never serve and tell.

07:06.817 --> 07:08.471
Good morning, Mike.
Table or counter today?

07:08.602 --> 07:10.865
Uh, neither, thanks.

07:10.995 --> 07:12.736
I'm actually
looking for Derek.

07:13.389 --> 07:15.304
I would love
to help you out,

07:15.391 --> 07:17.741
but Derek is a no-show
this morning.

07:18.133 --> 07:19.395
Probably overslept.

07:19.526 --> 07:20.744
Can I give him a message?

07:20.831 --> 07:23.268
No. No, thanks.
I'll catch him later.

07:23.355 --> 07:24.400
Well, at least
let me jump-start you

07:24.531 --> 07:25.357
with a cup of joe.

07:26.707 --> 07:27.925
Hey, Mike.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.101
Glad I ran into you.

07:30.841 --> 07:33.104
You know, I got those skates
that you called me about.

07:33.235 --> 07:34.584
So, is now a good time

07:34.715 --> 07:35.803
to come by the store
to pick 'em up?

07:37.326 --> 07:38.849
Uh, yeah, sure, why not?

07:38.936 --> 07:39.937
Okay, great.

07:41.330 --> 07:42.549
Marguerite's
gonna have you

07:42.679 --> 07:44.420
working your inside
edge in no time.

07:45.334 --> 07:46.596
[sighing]

07:46.727 --> 07:48.468
Five dollars a day,
new skater discount.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.687
And I'm gonna
waive the deposit

07:50.818 --> 07:53.298
as a thank you for getting
that stubborn young woman

07:53.429 --> 07:55.039
back into the dating pool.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.477
Oh, no, no, no. She...
[chuckling]

07:57.564 --> 07:59.740
She just agreed
to skating lessons.

07:59.870 --> 08:01.959
Every journey starts
with a single step.

08:02.090 --> 08:03.091
On ice.

08:03.221 --> 08:04.484
[chuckling]

08:05.572 --> 08:06.703
Whatever you say.

08:06.834 --> 08:08.575
Um, I guess
I will take it...

08:09.271 --> 08:10.490
Yeah, I'll-I'll take 'em
for the week.

08:10.620 --> 08:12.230
Okay, 35.

08:12.317 --> 08:14.189
[cash register beeping
and dinging]

08:16.017 --> 08:19.020
I couldn't help overhearing
you asking about Derek.

08:21.413 --> 08:22.763
Uh, yeah.

08:22.893 --> 08:25.330
Yeah, I-I just had
a question for him.

08:25.461 --> 08:28.072
Well, it's a shame he didn't
show up for work today.

08:28.203 --> 08:31.075
I really thought having a
regular job would turn him
around.

08:31.206 --> 08:32.381
Turn him around?

08:32.512 --> 08:35.384
Well, Derek's a troubled kid.

08:36.385 --> 08:38.039
Not a bad kid, mind you.

08:38.126 --> 08:39.475
Just...

08:39.606 --> 08:41.390
he has a lot of
difficulty fitting in.

08:41.999 --> 08:43.523
Doesn't have a lot
of friends and...

08:44.132 --> 08:46.090
and after his dad passed,

08:46.221 --> 08:48.397
his mom started
working two jobs.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.964
We got him the job at Mabel's

08:50.051 --> 08:52.009
through the Lakeside
Youth Initiative.

08:52.575 --> 08:54.969
Right, yeah, someone
did mention that you,

08:55.056 --> 08:56.666
you work with a youth group
or something?

08:56.797 --> 08:58.276
Yeah. Founder and

08:58.407 --> 09:00.583
Chairperson Emeritus
five terms.

09:00.670 --> 09:01.976
[chuckling]

09:03.238 --> 09:06.154
Okay, maybe... maybe you could
give me some advice then.

09:06.284 --> 09:09.157
Um, given your experience
with kids.

09:09.287 --> 09:10.593
Oh, ask away.

09:10.941 --> 09:12.247
Well...

09:13.509 --> 09:15.598
I may have seen Derek
do something he shouldn't have.

09:15.729 --> 09:16.991
Something serious?

09:17.992 --> 09:18.993
Yeah.

09:19.167 --> 09:20.690
♪

09:20.821 --> 09:23.301
I saw him jump out of
a window last night on Gorman.

09:24.128 --> 09:26.130
Which technically is
breaking and entering.

09:26.261 --> 09:27.305
Damn.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.351
-Yeah.
-Damn, damn.

09:29.481 --> 09:30.744
Stupid kid.

09:32.615 --> 09:35.313
And you decided not to go
to Chad about this?

09:36.967 --> 09:39.404
I saw you stewing outside
the police station.

09:40.144 --> 09:42.016
Right. Yeah, well, it could
be just a dumb prank.

09:42.973 --> 09:44.845
I think I know a cry for help
when I see one.

09:45.454 --> 09:47.064
So, what, you think I shouldn't
call the police?

09:47.195 --> 09:48.631
[sighing]

09:48.762 --> 09:50.415
Well, I'm not the one
who caught him in the act.

09:51.068 --> 09:53.070
I think it's a tough decision.

09:54.550 --> 09:55.464
Yeah.

09:58.206 --> 09:59.860
Well, thanks.

10:00.034 --> 10:01.122
♪

10:01.252 --> 10:02.732
You want to kill Wednesday.

10:02.993 --> 10:04.865
We wanna help you do that.

10:04.952 --> 10:07.215
You obviously have the resources
yourself to kill Wednesday.

10:07.781 --> 10:09.652
Why do you need Laura
to do your dirty work?

10:09.739 --> 10:11.001
This arrangement
is really between

10:11.132 --> 10:12.568
the young woman
and Mr. World.

10:12.655 --> 10:14.048
Maybe it's best you
wait out in the lobby.

10:14.178 --> 10:15.876
[rustling]

10:16.006 --> 10:17.747
I'm done waiting in lobbies.

10:21.838 --> 10:22.839
You haven't answered
my question.

10:22.970 --> 10:24.406
It's a delicate situation.

10:24.536 --> 10:25.929
[rustling]

10:26.060 --> 10:27.670
If we kill Wednesday,

10:28.236 --> 10:30.281
we start a war
that no one wants.

10:30.412 --> 10:33.981
However, if you were to do
the deed, it would be viewed
as a personal matter.

10:34.111 --> 10:37.114
An aggrieved party
settling a score.

10:37.767 --> 10:39.813
There would be no cause for the All-Father's compatriots

10:39.943 --> 10:41.641
to take up arms against us.

10:43.817 --> 10:44.861
It's a win-win.

10:44.948 --> 10:47.124
[whirring]

10:47.255 --> 10:48.952
[Laura]
See, the problem is,

10:49.083 --> 10:51.259
I don't have a way
to kill the old shitbag

10:51.389 --> 10:53.000
even if I did know
where the fuck he was.

10:53.391 --> 10:55.176
Nothing is out
of our reach.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.874
Oh, really? So, you can
get Odin's spear

10:58.005 --> 10:58.788
out of Sweeney's hoard?

10:58.919 --> 11:00.442
[whirring]

11:00.572 --> 11:01.835
It can be done.

11:02.444 --> 11:04.751
Well, then,
sign me the fuck up.

11:05.665 --> 11:06.709
[slamming]

11:12.323 --> 11:14.543
I need to, uh,
speak to my client.

11:14.717 --> 11:15.979
♪

11:16.110 --> 11:17.285
[door bell ringing]

11:22.594 --> 11:25.336
-[knocking]
-Derek!

11:25.728 --> 11:27.687
I know you saw me last night.

11:29.689 --> 11:31.865
But believe it or not,
I'm here to help.

11:31.995 --> 11:32.953
[footsteps approaching]

11:36.957 --> 11:37.871
Listen, uh...

11:46.183 --> 11:48.055
You know, I-I never
featured you for a snitch.

11:48.185 --> 11:50.231
You know, this goes a lot
better for you, Derek,

11:50.361 --> 11:52.494
if you just tell me
what happened to Alison.

11:52.624 --> 11:53.843
Wh... Alison?

11:53.974 --> 11:55.105
Wh...

11:55.845 --> 11:58.108
-Alison and I were cool.
-Hum...

11:58.239 --> 12:00.197
Look, I-I-I would never
fuck with her, never.

12:00.328 --> 12:02.896
Okay? And-and the night
that she disappeared,

12:03.026 --> 12:04.724
I was working
a double shift. Okay?

12:04.811 --> 12:05.899
And then, I went home

12:06.029 --> 12:07.422
and I watched
the old tube with my mom.

12:07.552 --> 12:09.163
So, I-I haven't done
anything wrong.

12:09.293 --> 12:10.207
All right?

12:15.996 --> 12:17.345
[clearing throat]

12:17.475 --> 12:20.740
Okay, uh, I-I may have went
into a couple of houses.

12:20.870 --> 12:22.829
Eleven, by my count.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.396
You broke into where
people live, Derek,

12:25.875 --> 12:26.876
where they sleep.

12:27.007 --> 12:29.052
I mean, God,
you're stealing panties,

12:29.183 --> 12:30.401
for Chrissake.

12:30.488 --> 12:31.576
Terrorizing
the entire town.

12:31.663 --> 12:33.013
Terr-terrori...?

12:33.840 --> 12:36.581
I-I like to wear female shit
sometimes, okay?

12:36.712 --> 12:38.279
What, you want me
to walk into Galecki's,

12:38.409 --> 12:39.976
buy myself a little
push-up bra and a thong?

12:40.107 --> 12:41.717
Yeah, yeah, that'd go over big
in this little fuckin' town.

12:41.891 --> 12:43.719
♪

12:43.850 --> 12:45.547
See, see that's what
I'm talking about.
Right there! Right there!

12:45.677 --> 12:47.027
He thinks I'm a fucking fag
or somethin'!

12:47.157 --> 12:50.595
I-I... I don't care
if you are a...

12:50.682 --> 12:52.641
a boy or a girl, or...

12:52.772 --> 12:55.209
or-or-or both, or-or neither.

12:55.296 --> 12:57.559
Okay? I-I don't get it,
but I don't have to!

12:57.689 --> 13:00.692
What you did is a crime!

13:00.823 --> 13:03.217
So, what, I'm-I'm just, I'm
just straight-up fucked then.

13:03.347 --> 13:05.132
Even though I had nothing
to do with this Alison shit.

13:08.091 --> 13:09.789
Chad's willing
to make you a deal.

13:10.746 --> 13:11.965
[sighing]

13:20.364 --> 13:22.584
Back in my country, I was
an excellent businessman.

13:22.714 --> 13:25.021
Allow me to negotiate
the terms and conditions.

13:25.282 --> 13:27.110
Um, just out of curiosity,

13:27.197 --> 13:29.286
were assassination attempts
your speciality?

13:29.417 --> 13:31.375
No, of course not,
but in Oman,

13:31.506 --> 13:32.942
a verbal contract
is binding.

13:33.073 --> 13:34.117
And from everything
I've seen here,

13:34.248 --> 13:35.510
it's the same with gods.

13:35.640 --> 13:37.512
Once the terms are set,
they can't be undone.

13:38.034 --> 13:39.166
Now is not the time
to be impulsive.

13:40.210 --> 13:41.124
Impulsive?

13:42.517 --> 13:43.648
Because I know
what I want?

13:44.214 --> 13:46.129
This is not Oman, Salim.

13:46.477 --> 13:49.045
In America,
women can drive cars.

13:49.480 --> 13:51.091
They even let us vote,

13:51.221 --> 13:52.962
and some of us can negotiate
our own fuckin' deals.

13:53.093 --> 13:54.921
Women can do all
those things in Oman!

13:55.486 --> 13:56.661
And you know me
well enough to understand

13:56.792 --> 13:58.272
this is not what I mean
by impulsive.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.058
I value our friendship.

14:02.798 --> 14:04.539
I care about your well-being.

14:05.453 --> 14:07.281
And I don't want you
to end up like Sweeney

14:08.021 --> 14:10.632
or the Jinn, who sold
their souls to the devil.

14:11.111 --> 14:12.112
And for what?

14:13.330 --> 14:14.636
Okay. Fine.

14:16.594 --> 14:17.987
-Okay?
-Okay.

14:21.904 --> 14:24.167
♪

14:27.692 --> 14:28.824
[car door opening]

14:36.614 --> 14:37.833
Cordelia?

14:37.964 --> 14:39.095
Hey! What the hell
are you doing here?

14:39.226 --> 14:40.444
Wednesday sent me
to find you.

14:40.575 --> 14:42.011
He said it'd be safe here.

14:42.098 --> 14:43.230
I went to your house
but you weren't there,

14:43.317 --> 14:44.274
so I came into town.

14:44.361 --> 14:45.580
Okay. Calm down.
Slow down.

14:47.843 --> 14:49.801
Why'd he send you here?
What... Safe from what?

14:49.932 --> 14:51.499
When my boss announces
he's a god

14:51.629 --> 14:53.283
and someone is killing
his followers,

14:53.414 --> 14:55.155
which apparently explains
why it's partly cloudy

14:55.285 --> 14:56.417
with a chance
of human remains!

14:56.547 --> 14:57.461
I mean, what the fuck?

14:57.592 --> 14:58.810
All right, um...

14:59.550 --> 15:01.422
Look, I'm not asking
if he's crazy.

15:01.901 --> 15:04.294
We both know he's
bat shit out of his tree.

15:05.469 --> 15:07.471
I need to know if any of what
he told me is true.

15:12.476 --> 15:13.825
-Oh, my God.
-Come on.

15:13.956 --> 15:15.218
You're probably cold.
Come on.

15:15.349 --> 15:16.828
Oh, my God. All of this
is real, isn't it?

15:16.916 --> 15:18.482
-It's okay. It's okay.
-I answered a fucking ad.

15:18.569 --> 15:20.093
It was cash
under the table.

15:20.223 --> 15:21.964
Dude wasn't trying
to get in my pants.

15:22.095 --> 15:23.270
One minute
I'm trying to explain

15:23.400 --> 15:24.532
where all the payphones went,

15:24.662 --> 15:26.447
and then a flaming body
hits the asphalt

15:26.534 --> 15:28.057
and he's telling me to chill
about all these murders

15:28.188 --> 15:29.450
because he's
a thousand years old

15:29.580 --> 15:31.234
-and kicks it with warlocks.
-Shh. Hey, hey. Shh.

15:31.365 --> 15:32.844
Okay. I get it. I get it.

15:32.975 --> 15:35.108
Okay, believe me.
I was you.

15:35.238 --> 15:37.240
Okay? Not too long ago.
Up was up, down was down,

15:37.371 --> 15:38.676
and then everything
in my life, it just...

15:39.590 --> 15:40.591
...it exploded.

15:41.592 --> 15:42.811
Okay, but...

15:42.942 --> 15:44.204
I didn't have anyone
I could talk to.

15:44.334 --> 15:45.422
You have me.

15:48.469 --> 15:50.384
And you are what, exactly?

15:51.385 --> 15:53.865
I don't... the jury's
still out on that, okay?

15:55.084 --> 15:56.520
Where is he?

15:56.651 --> 16:00.611
Uh, he said he wanted to get
a line on a berserker?

16:01.177 --> 16:02.439
He wants me to wait here,

16:02.570 --> 16:04.180
but I did not make
any promises.

16:04.876 --> 16:06.139
Okay, good.

16:07.314 --> 16:08.880
All right. Come on.
We've got a lot to talk about.

16:09.446 --> 16:10.404
[sighing]

16:11.405 --> 16:12.580
We will tell you

16:12.710 --> 16:13.885
the time and the place
of the attack.

16:14.538 --> 16:16.671
♪

16:16.801 --> 16:19.369
Agreed. However,
you must provide

16:19.500 --> 16:20.936
immediate extraction
from the scene

16:21.067 --> 16:22.546
to ensure Laura's safety.

16:22.894 --> 16:24.766
Furthermore,
once the target

16:24.896 --> 16:26.724
has been eliminated,
you, your allies,

16:26.855 --> 16:28.683
officiates, and surrogates
shall furnish

16:28.813 --> 16:30.119
24-hour protection for her

16:30.250 --> 16:31.468
from any and all parties

16:31.599 --> 16:33.775
seeking retribution
or retaliation.

16:34.123 --> 16:35.255
Not a problem.

16:35.385 --> 16:37.083
Upon completion
of the assignment,

16:37.213 --> 16:39.389
my client will have
no further obligation to you,

16:39.476 --> 16:41.957
your successors,
heirs, or assignees.

16:42.523 --> 16:43.828
Sounds like you don't trust us.

16:43.959 --> 16:46.266
We will need these terms
and conditions memorialized

16:46.353 --> 16:48.094
in a document binding
on both parties.

16:51.010 --> 16:52.576
Agreed and accepted.

16:52.707 --> 16:53.621
I think we're done here.

16:53.751 --> 16:55.884
Uh, wait.
One more thing.

16:56.798 --> 16:59.192
That protection also
has to cover Salim

16:59.322 --> 17:00.497
and one other person.

17:00.628 --> 17:01.716
Shadow Moon.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.417
Why not?

17:08.201 --> 17:10.725
However, if you should fail
to hold up on your end,

17:11.117 --> 17:13.728
you will die and
your friends'll die.

17:16.296 --> 17:17.210
I accept.

17:18.863 --> 17:20.082
You can't do this.

17:20.169 --> 17:22.215
Salim, I'm not gonna
fuck this up.

17:27.742 --> 17:28.830
Hmm...

17:29.396 --> 17:30.614
Now we do have a deal.

17:32.747 --> 17:35.402
The phone's GPS will direct you
to your first location.

17:35.532 --> 17:37.317
Once there, you will
receive instructions

17:37.447 --> 17:38.840
on how to acquire
the spear.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.450
Uh, what about expenses?

17:40.581 --> 17:42.148
You can tap that.

17:43.105 --> 17:44.063
Okay.

17:47.457 --> 17:48.371
Godspeed.

17:49.329 --> 17:50.330
Eat a dick.

17:50.460 --> 17:52.723
[laughing]

17:59.600 --> 18:00.557
[knocking on door]

18:12.613 --> 18:14.745
Thank the gods
you're okay, huh?

18:15.529 --> 18:18.227
Now, where's Cordelia, huh?

18:18.358 --> 18:19.750
She's in the shower.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.665
Your whole coming-out routine

18:21.796 --> 18:23.276
really fucked her brain up
pretty good. What's goin' on?

18:23.406 --> 18:25.191
Some blood-craving berserker,

18:25.321 --> 18:26.801
who was once signed
to protect me,

18:26.888 --> 18:30.283
has lost whatever his last
tenuous grip was on reality,

18:30.413 --> 18:32.372
and, I don't know,
due to psychedelics,

18:32.502 --> 18:33.764
brain fever,
the curse of Fu Manchu,

18:33.895 --> 18:35.201
who knows anyway,

18:35.331 --> 18:37.812
lately, he's taken to
slaughtering my followers.

18:38.552 --> 18:39.683
It's fine.
I'm not a follower.

18:39.814 --> 18:41.076
No, you are not.

18:41.207 --> 18:42.947
You're my son.
Which is why you need

18:43.078 --> 18:44.949
to come with us
until this has been resolved.

18:45.080 --> 18:45.907
All right, look, I'm...

18:48.083 --> 18:50.477
I wouldn't count on Cordelia
as a travel companion.

18:51.217 --> 18:53.001
Okay? And I'm definitely not
gonna just drop everything here

18:53.132 --> 18:54.133
to get on the road
with you again.

18:55.873 --> 18:57.440
Because you have met someone.

18:57.701 --> 18:59.834
♪

19:00.791 --> 19:02.793
I dunno what your little
birds have told you.

19:04.491 --> 19:05.840
What I have learned...

19:07.885 --> 19:09.235
...is that cruel fate

19:10.801 --> 19:12.673
gives us few opportunities

19:14.544 --> 19:16.851
to totally connect
with the soul of another.

19:19.854 --> 19:21.508
Cordelia did say
things didn't work out

19:21.638 --> 19:22.596
with you and Demeter.

19:22.726 --> 19:23.901
Sadly, no.

19:25.381 --> 19:26.426
-[door creaking]
-It's a shame.

19:28.428 --> 19:29.342
Hmm.

19:31.213 --> 19:34.085
If you do stay, promise me
you'll be vigilant?

19:35.478 --> 19:36.392
Yeah.

19:37.480 --> 19:39.003
Aren't you in danger, too?

19:39.090 --> 19:40.440
I haven't been around
for millennia

19:40.570 --> 19:42.268
without learning
how to fend for myself.

19:43.965 --> 19:45.184
[Shadow]
Ah, now look, if you...

19:47.011 --> 19:49.840
If you need me, and I mean
really need me...

19:52.234 --> 19:53.104
...you call.

19:56.020 --> 19:58.066
[floor creaking]

19:58.197 --> 19:59.546
Cordelia, my dear.

20:01.417 --> 20:03.158
I realize recent developments

20:03.245 --> 20:06.248
have brought forth
some disturbing truths.

20:06.335 --> 20:08.903
Heh.
Disturbing truths.

20:09.033 --> 20:10.818
Don't you think that's
kind of an understatement?

20:10.948 --> 20:12.733
Oh, well.
That's his specialty.

20:12.863 --> 20:14.865
It's a... it's a lot
to take in.

20:14.996 --> 20:16.215
Indeed.

20:17.085 --> 20:20.044
I rarely make mistakes
in my personnel selection,

20:20.175 --> 20:22.743
but under the circumstances,

20:23.700 --> 20:25.702
I'm releasing you from
any contractual obligations

20:25.833 --> 20:27.530
-you might have to...
-Oh, oh, oh, oh!

20:27.661 --> 20:29.445
You-you get me jammed up
in this creep show,

20:29.576 --> 20:31.534
-and now you're firing me?
-No, no, no, no, no.

20:31.665 --> 20:32.840
I'm giving you a choice.

20:35.146 --> 20:36.409
And if I choose
to stay put?

20:37.323 --> 20:38.367
Wait, what?

20:38.498 --> 20:40.326
That's my girl, huh?

20:40.891 --> 20:41.936
Well, you get dressed.
I'll wait for you

20:42.066 --> 20:43.154
in the car, okay?
And you...

20:44.504 --> 20:45.592
You stay safe, huh?

20:47.855 --> 20:48.769
[footsteps receding]

20:48.856 --> 20:49.813
[door opening]

20:50.771 --> 20:51.728
Hey.

20:51.859 --> 20:52.773
[door closing]

20:54.165 --> 20:55.254
[gasping]

20:55.384 --> 20:56.646
You don't owe him anything.

20:58.648 --> 20:59.997
And-and just so you know,

21:00.128 --> 21:01.390
this doesn't get
any less dangerous.

21:02.130 --> 21:03.436
So what?

21:04.045 --> 21:06.265
I'm just supposed to go back
to business as usual

21:06.395 --> 21:07.788
knowing gods walk among us?

21:09.268 --> 21:10.225
I can't do that.

21:12.140 --> 21:13.228
Any more than you can.

21:19.408 --> 21:20.366
[door closing]

21:20.975 --> 21:22.063
Fuck...

21:22.237 --> 21:24.239
♪

21:26.197 --> 21:29.810
[woman singing opera]

22:03.278 --> 22:05.498
[Ibis]
"Bilquis arrived in this land

22:05.628 --> 22:07.891
a deity in full.

22:08.022 --> 22:12.679
The avatar of Sheba,
a queen, Goddess of love.

22:13.114 --> 22:14.594
Or was she?

22:14.724 --> 22:16.465
Her worshippers
told her as much,

22:16.596 --> 22:18.249
though perhaps
they were communicating

22:18.380 --> 22:20.208
what they needed her to be.

22:21.383 --> 22:24.821
Then, through the intercession
of the Orishas,

22:24.952 --> 22:28.999
our divine sister identified
who she was not.

22:29.565 --> 22:31.872
But before one can step
into the light

22:32.002 --> 22:33.917
of one's own truth,
one must first

22:34.048 --> 22:36.267
determine what that truth is.

22:36.398 --> 22:39.183
Quo vadis, as the Romans say.

22:39.270 --> 22:41.403
Where are you going?
And why?"

22:42.448 --> 22:43.884
Sisters,

22:44.798 --> 22:47.235
let the spirit of the "we"
guide me

22:47.366 --> 22:48.845
-to divine right action...
-[exhaling]

22:48.976 --> 22:51.892
...in word and deed
to spread the knowledge

22:52.762 --> 22:54.895
that in the strength
of the many

22:55.765 --> 22:57.898
lies the power
of the one love.

22:58.333 --> 23:00.509
♪

23:05.862 --> 23:06.863
[whirring]

23:07.298 --> 23:08.561
[animalistic growling]

23:08.691 --> 23:09.562
[baby crying]

23:14.480 --> 23:15.959
[panting]

23:23.097 --> 23:24.315
♪

23:24.403 --> 23:25.665
[skates gliding]

23:30.757 --> 23:32.846
You got this.
There you go.

23:32.976 --> 23:34.456
Come on, eyes up.
Come on.

23:35.370 --> 23:36.806
Yeah, I-I... I read

23:36.937 --> 23:38.939
that ice is harder
than concrete.

23:39.069 --> 23:40.506
Don't think about the ice.

23:40.636 --> 23:42.464
Think about
bending your knees,

23:42.595 --> 23:44.161
keeping your weight centered.

23:44.292 --> 23:46.599
Relax your shoulders.
Whoa!

23:47.164 --> 23:49.428
Okay, ah!
What happened?

23:49.558 --> 23:51.821
What happened? I was totally
concentrating on relaxing.

23:51.952 --> 23:53.606
Concentrate less,
relax more.

23:54.650 --> 23:55.999
And try not to face plant.

23:56.130 --> 23:57.044
Thanks.

23:59.873 --> 24:01.527
Okay.
Let's try this.

24:03.050 --> 24:05.139
There you go.
Follow me.

24:09.273 --> 24:12.276
I was wondering
if you might wanna... Oh!

24:12.842 --> 24:15.062
-Steady.
-Ha! Ha! ...grab dinner
after this.

24:17.543 --> 24:19.849
As-as like a thank you
for the lesson.

24:22.373 --> 24:24.288
You know, y-you and Leon can
come, of course.

24:29.511 --> 24:31.905
Leon's got a sleepover tonight,

24:32.035 --> 24:34.864
but if you don't mind
having dinner with just me?

24:36.910 --> 24:38.477
-Whoa! Whoa!
-[laughing]

24:39.695 --> 24:41.001
-Yup.
-I've got ya.

24:41.349 --> 24:42.350
Uh.

24:43.394 --> 24:44.483
Yeah.

24:44.831 --> 24:45.788
That works for me.

24:51.141 --> 24:52.360
How about we try letting go?

24:54.101 --> 24:56.407
Yeah, I...
Not sure I'm ready.

24:56.538 --> 24:57.844
[laughing]

25:00.673 --> 25:01.630
You got this.

25:09.812 --> 25:11.118
It's easy.

25:11.640 --> 25:13.816
You, Mike Ainsel,
are a miracle on ice.

25:20.040 --> 25:21.171
♪

25:22.346 --> 25:24.348
[rumbling]

25:25.915 --> 25:27.395
[rumbling]

25:31.747 --> 25:32.661
[grunting]

25:33.401 --> 25:34.968
[exhaling]

25:35.708 --> 25:36.796
[grunting]

25:47.676 --> 25:49.896
♪

25:53.682 --> 25:54.596
[coin clinking]

25:56.424 --> 25:57.468
[sizzling]

26:08.218 --> 26:09.350
Mike?
[laughing]

26:09.480 --> 26:11.134
You really ate it.

26:11.787 --> 26:13.354
Did you... did you
see that coin?

26:14.877 --> 26:16.400
Hey. Are you okay?

26:17.837 --> 26:18.838
Did you hit your head?

26:19.839 --> 26:20.927
No, I'm... I'm fine.

26:25.018 --> 26:27.063
I think you better
stay put for a minute.

26:27.803 --> 26:29.457
Then, a cup of hot cocoa
will fix you right up.

26:33.722 --> 26:36.377
♪

26:49.477 --> 26:50.609
♪ All right ♪

26:51.348 --> 26:52.523
♪ Yeah ♪

26:53.133 --> 26:54.787
♪ Tell me why did you
have to go ♪

26:55.178 --> 26:56.876
[baby crying]

26:56.963 --> 27:00.619
♪ Girl I'm 'bout to fall away ♪

27:00.706 --> 27:02.882
♪ To get you back ♪

27:04.623 --> 27:07.756
♪ So good to fall away ♪

27:08.714 --> 27:11.325
♪ To get you back ♪
♪ Oh yeah ♪

27:12.543 --> 27:14.589
[indistinct chatter]

27:15.285 --> 27:16.809
[muffled conversations]

27:23.859 --> 27:26.470
Hi! Welcome
to the party!

27:26.601 --> 27:28.211
[chuckling]

27:28.342 --> 27:29.517
I'm Melody.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.824
I'm... Bilquis.

27:32.912 --> 27:36.567
I... believe I'm supposed
to meet someone here.

27:36.698 --> 27:39.005
Well, there's a lot
of someones here, so...

27:39.614 --> 27:41.094
[growling, baby crying]

27:41.224 --> 27:42.008
That's her.

27:43.966 --> 27:45.141
Eugenia?

27:45.620 --> 27:47.535
Everybody loves Eugenia.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.232
Even though she's
quite a handful,

27:49.319 --> 27:50.538
especially
since she got sick.

27:50.669 --> 27:52.932
Eugenia.
Will you excuse me?

27:54.760 --> 27:56.022
You might wanna go easy.

27:59.808 --> 28:00.679
Eugenia?

28:03.246 --> 28:05.988
I believe that you and I
have something to talk about.

28:07.511 --> 28:09.035
Well, isn't that fine.

28:09.383 --> 28:10.776
Now give me back my plate.

28:11.298 --> 28:13.561
-I'm here because--
-I know why you're here.

28:13.692 --> 28:16.477
And I'll tell you
what I've been telling
Pastor Jenkins:

28:16.607 --> 28:18.653
I know I'm dying,

28:19.306 --> 28:21.264
but he got to stop sending
you church ladies here

28:21.395 --> 28:22.744
with your smiley ways

28:22.875 --> 28:24.224
to hurry me
off to my reward.

28:24.311 --> 28:25.921
I'm not from--

28:26.052 --> 28:28.402
I appreciate all the church
has done for the community,

28:29.185 --> 28:31.361
even though I don't buy
the product you're selling,

28:31.448 --> 28:35.191
but I've still got business
to see to in this life.

28:35.583 --> 28:37.106
So you go about
your business!

28:37.237 --> 28:39.152
But first, give me
back my plate!

28:44.853 --> 28:47.508
♪

28:55.951 --> 28:57.474
♪

28:57.561 --> 28:58.649
[Bilquis]
Oshun?

28:58.780 --> 29:00.695
It's difficult
to invite someone

29:00.782 --> 29:02.175
to be a part of something

29:02.305 --> 29:05.047
until you are a part
of it yourself.

29:11.314 --> 29:13.316
♪

29:13.708 --> 29:15.144
I tried to warn you.

29:15.275 --> 29:18.060
Eugenia's always
been direct, but lately...

29:18.669 --> 29:20.584
her bite is like
a junkyard dog.

29:20.715 --> 29:22.673
She's a kitty cat
next to my auntie.

29:22.761 --> 29:24.066
When she tears a strip off you,

29:24.197 --> 29:25.546
you best get yourself
checked for rabies.

29:25.633 --> 29:27.461
[laughing]

29:27.591 --> 29:29.898
Come. Let's get some cake.

29:31.204 --> 29:35.643
♪ I got to find a way to get
this New Orleans back ♪

29:38.777 --> 29:41.518
♪ I can't stand it no longer ♪

29:44.695 --> 29:45.958
[door closing]

29:49.657 --> 29:51.833
Hey, if this Johan guy's
so dangerous,

29:51.964 --> 29:53.487
why do you think talking
to him's gonna help?

29:53.617 --> 29:54.967
I may not talk to him.

29:55.097 --> 29:56.795
I may just fucking kill him.

29:59.188 --> 30:00.102
Come on.

30:00.929 --> 30:02.104
Oh, yeah.

30:05.368 --> 30:06.892
♪

30:07.022 --> 30:09.372
[knife slashing]

30:12.332 --> 30:13.507
Dunker!

30:14.029 --> 30:16.162
Dunk!
There you are, huh?

30:16.292 --> 30:17.903
Geirvaldr!
[chuckling]

30:17.990 --> 30:18.947
It's been so long.

30:19.992 --> 30:20.906
It has indeed.

30:22.472 --> 30:25.214
When last we met,
you had just done a widow

30:25.301 --> 30:28.261
out of her last cent
and had eaten her goat.

30:28.391 --> 30:30.393
Yeah, if I wasn't so full,

30:30.524 --> 30:32.134
I-I would have eaten
her kid, too.

30:33.266 --> 30:35.268
"Kid" as in baby goat?

30:35.398 --> 30:36.965
[laughing]
Yeah.

30:37.096 --> 30:38.837
Such a roly-poly boy.

30:38.967 --> 30:40.273
You know, the fat ones,

30:40.403 --> 30:42.101
they're always- they're always
best for eatin'.

30:42.405 --> 30:44.190
Anyway, I'm here
to see your tenant.

30:48.455 --> 30:50.631
Wait here. And remember
if you touch anything,

30:50.761 --> 30:52.067
you'll need a tetanus shot.

30:52.198 --> 30:53.852
[flies buzzing]

30:57.246 --> 30:58.857
Rules are rules, All-Father.

30:59.205 --> 31:00.641
-Even for you.
-Of course.

31:00.771 --> 31:02.121
And rules need to be obeyed.

31:02.251 --> 31:03.426
Proceed.

31:04.384 --> 31:07.300
Speech it spoils,
yet speech it frees.

31:08.649 --> 31:10.607
Hmm. Booze perhaps?

31:13.088 --> 31:15.177
Dunker, you gotta
do better than that.

31:15.308 --> 31:16.875
Thank you. Huh.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.399
Jesus.
We could all use a drink.

31:20.835 --> 31:22.619
♪

31:22.750 --> 31:23.925
[neon crackling]

31:29.670 --> 31:31.498
[flies buzzing]

32:07.403 --> 32:10.232
[knife cutting]

32:10.406 --> 32:12.234
♪

32:12.365 --> 32:14.976
Johan is not there.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.674
Yeah.
Went out a while ago.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.676
And you didn't think
to mention that to me

32:19.763 --> 32:20.982
before I went upstairs.

32:23.506 --> 32:25.030
I like to do the riddles.

32:25.552 --> 32:26.770
[Mr. Wednesday]
Any idea where he's gone?

32:26.901 --> 32:28.468
I dunno. He said something
about going to a dentist.

32:28.642 --> 32:30.557
♪

32:31.688 --> 32:33.081
Cordelia, we're outta here.

32:34.604 --> 32:36.258
[knife cutting]

32:36.389 --> 32:38.565
Hey, what would happen
if he didn't answer the riddle?

32:38.695 --> 32:40.523
Oh, I-I would've got
to cut out his tongue.

32:41.872 --> 32:42.743
[gasping in disgust]

32:46.660 --> 32:49.228
♪ But I'm the girl who's
getting...♪

32:50.881 --> 32:53.754
[indistinct chatter]

32:58.063 --> 33:01.501
♪ Come on,
and give it back ♪

33:01.675 --> 33:06.593
♪ Won't you give it back♪

33:06.767 --> 33:10.989
♪

33:11.163 --> 33:14.949
♪ Then you come back to me
saying I'm no good ♪

33:15.123 --> 33:20.781
♪ Tell me where... ♪

33:20.868 --> 33:21.782
[stomping]

33:25.133 --> 33:26.395
[rumbling]

33:28.963 --> 33:32.140
♪

33:41.236 --> 33:42.933
♪

34:57.007 --> 34:58.748
♪

35:00.533 --> 35:03.057
♪

35:03.188 --> 35:05.668
[murmuring indistinctly]

35:06.060 --> 35:07.714
[grunting]

35:09.411 --> 35:11.283
[low growling]

35:12.588 --> 35:14.460
Johan.

35:14.547 --> 35:17.550
[demonic murmuring]

35:17.680 --> 35:19.117
You don't want to do this.

35:19.247 --> 35:21.597
Turn around, walk away.

35:21.728 --> 35:24.034
[demonic murmuring]

35:25.471 --> 35:26.341
[growling]

35:29.083 --> 35:30.867
♪

35:37.613 --> 35:38.701
[sighing]

35:41.530 --> 35:42.401
[exhaling]

35:42.575 --> 35:45.186
♪

35:46.883 --> 35:48.407
[chuckling]

35:48.537 --> 35:52.367
I can't believe
I didn't recognize you.

35:52.498 --> 35:54.587
I had to show you
who I was.

35:54.717 --> 35:55.805
[laughing]

35:56.937 --> 35:58.547
♪

36:02.421 --> 36:04.466
I'm not ready to
leave this life yet.

36:04.988 --> 36:06.816
Go harvest your souls
somewhere else.

36:06.947 --> 36:07.861
Shoo!

36:19.089 --> 36:20.090
[gasping]

36:25.618 --> 36:26.662
You were there.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.099
You were with Shadow Moon.

36:29.230 --> 36:30.536
Yes, I was.

36:30.927 --> 36:32.886
I midwifed him
into this world.

36:33.626 --> 36:36.542
Mother Yemoja
guiding my hands.

36:42.374 --> 36:44.027
His father was angry.

36:44.550 --> 36:45.942
Bound to these shores.

36:47.770 --> 36:49.468
I didn't like
breaking up a family,

36:49.598 --> 36:51.034
but he would've
destroyed that boy.

36:51.948 --> 36:53.689
Shadow Moon is a man now.

36:54.995 --> 36:56.344
But he still
needs our help.

36:57.084 --> 36:58.346
Your help.

36:58.781 --> 37:01.436
Only you have the power
to find The Other.

37:02.611 --> 37:03.743
The Other?

37:04.309 --> 37:06.006
Shadow Moon's
only one-half.

37:06.702 --> 37:09.052
He cannot lead the people,
the "we" alone.

37:09.401 --> 37:11.490
You must find The Other.

37:12.621 --> 37:15.798
If you do not, the people
can never come together,

37:16.625 --> 37:19.454
and these will be
our last days.

